attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, for GNU/Linux 2.6.9, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a Linux backdoor/RAT. It establishes persistence by creating shell scripts in cron directories (`/etc/cron.hourly/%s.sh`) and init.d startup locations (`/etc/init.d/%s`, `/etc/rc%d.d/S90%s`). It communicates with a C2 server over HTTP, using fake `User-Agent` headers (`Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE...`, `Wget/1.12...`). It gathers system information by reading from `/proc/net/tcp` and `/proc/%d/exe`, and reads its configuration from `/etc/daemon.cfg`.
